'''Geoffrey Mark Dent-Brocklehurst''' (25 April 1932 – 9 September 1972) was a British [[stockbroker]] and the [[heir]] to [[Sudeley Castle]].<ref name="times">{{cite news |title=Mr Mark Dent Brocklehurst |work=[[The Times]] |publisher=The Times Digital Archive |page= 19 |date=14 September 1972 }}</ref><ref>[http://iccoventry.icnetwork.co.uk/0100news/features/midlandrichlist/page.cfm?objectid=12273375&method=full&siteid=50002 Lady Ashcombe & Family £50m] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040914143236/http://iccoventry.icnetwork.co.uk/0100news/features/midlandrichlist/page.cfm?objectid=12273375&method=full&siteid=50002 |date=2004-09-14 }}, iccoventry.icnetwork.co.uk; accessed 2 April 2016.</ref> He was the son of Major John Henry Dent-Brocklehurst and his wife, Mary (''née'' Morrison). Via his paternal grandmother, Marion Lascelles, he is a descendant of [[Henry Lascelles, 3rd Earl of Harewood]]. Thus he was a third cousin of [[George Lascelles, 7th Earl of Harewood]]. [[Michael Hicks Beach, 2nd Earl St Aldwyn]], whose mother was Marjorie Brocklehurst, was his first cousin.{{cn|date=April 2016}}
Dent-Brocklehurst died suddenly from a [[heart attack]] in 1972, aged 40.<ref>[http://history.sudeleycastle.co.uk/era.php?e=8 Sudeley Castle History] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071108225715/http://history.sudeleycastle.co.uk/era.php?e=8 |date=2007-11-08 }}</ref> The castle passed to his wife, Mary Elizabeth (''née'' Chipps), and their two children,<ref name="guardian">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2012/jun/01/tea-lady-ashcombe-emma-kennedy?newsfeed=true|title=Emma's Eccentric Britain: afternoon tea with Lady Ashcombe|date=1 June 2012|work=[[The Guardian]]|author=Emma Kennedy|accessdate=25 March 2016}}</ref> Henry and [[Mollie Dent-Brocklehurst|Mollie]]. His wife remarried [[Henry Cubitt, 4th Baron Ashcombe]], in 1979.
==Ancestry== {{ahnentafel |collapsed=yes |align=center |boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc; |boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9; |boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc; |boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc; |boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe; |1=1. '''Mark Dent-Brocklehurst''' |2=2. Major John Henry Dent-Brocklehurst |3=3. Mary Morrison |4=4. Captain Henry Dent Brocklehurst |5=5. Marion Lascelles |6=6. Lt.-Col. James Archibald Morrison |7=7. Hon. Mary Hill-Trevor |8=8. Henry Brocklehurst |9=9. Anne Fielden |10=10. Hon. Egremont William Lascelles |11=11. Jessie Elizabeth Malcolm |12=12. Alfred Morrison |13=13. Mabel Chermside |14=14. [[Edwin Hill-Trevor, 1st Baron Trevor]] |15=15. Hon. Mary Catherine Curzon |16=16. John Brocklehurst |17=17. Mary Coare |18=18. John Fielden |20=20. [[Henry Lascelles, 3rd Earl of Harewood]] |21=21. Lady Louisa Thynne |22=22. Neil Malcolm, 13th of Poltalloch |23=23. Harriet Mary Clarke-Jervoise |24=24. James Morrison |25=25. Mary Anne Todd |26=26. Rev. R. S. C. Chermside |28=28. [[Arthur Hill, 3rd Marquess of Downshire]] |29=29. Lady Mary Windsor |30=30. Rev. Hon. Alfred Curzon |31=31. Sophia Holden }}
