{{unreferenced|date=September 2008}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = | name = Otto II | title = Bishop of Utrecht | image = Otto ii van lippe.jpg | alt = | caption = Otto II of Lippe curses Rudolf of Coevorden. | church = [[Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = [[Archdiocese of Utrecht (695–1580)|Archdiocese of Utrecht]] | see = | term = 1216–1227 | predecessor = | successor = <!-- Orders --> | ordination = | ordained_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | cardinal = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = 28 July 1228 | death_place = | previous_post = | nationality = }}
'''Otto of Lippe''' was a son of [[Bernhard II, Lord of Lippe]]. He was [[Archdiocese of Utrecht (695–1580)|bishop of Utrecht]] as Otto II from 1216 to 1227. Several of his brothers also held high ecclesiastical offices in the Rhineland.
During the [[Fifth Crusade]], Otto visited [[Palestine (region)|Palestine]].
In 1227, Otto was joined by his former enemy, count [[Floris IV, Count of Holland]], to suppress a rebellion by the people of [[Drenthe]], led by [[Rudolph van Coevorden]]. He died in the [[Battle of Ane]] (a town close to [[Hardenberg]]) on July 28, 1227. {{Commons category|Otto II of Lippe}}
